				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Our Job...who knows it us or the casters?<a name="6511"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 20 03 11:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, just gotta let off some steam.  Its seems to be a trend lately that other peeps seem to &quot;THINK&quot; they know how to play a bard better then us bards.  (I have discussed this with a few other bard friends and they have experienced the same)  Lately I have been getting alot of tells from peeps saying play this or play that or why isn't this in your twist..etc etc.   On top of that they say &quot;stop being lazy and keep your twist going&quot;  Yet little do they know...if you are the primary slower (and usually have to use OOS before trying to land Requiem of Time becuase of the recast delay) the twist can't start up right away...and heaven forbid they don't have mana song up for a whole 6 seconds.  
<br />
  I hate HATE HATE, when peeps demand certain songs for the group...I can understand if someone has a request, but h*ll with over 2 years exp and 65 levels I would think I have a handle on how to play the class and have a little more knowledge and experience then they do, even though they have &quot;a level 22 Bard&quot; (seems to be every swinging *$#@ has a high teen low 20 bard twink that just got too hard for them to play and yet they still think they are experts because they have about 10hours of playtime as a bard)
<br />
  Sorry...I am really not that bitter, and don't get me wrong I love playing my bard, its by far the most interesting class in the game, but just had a bad experience last night with a few peeps in a group and needed to vent to other bards to see if others have any problems like this or am I just hosed up.
<br />

<br />
Keys
<br />
65 Bard Stormhammer
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
