				<td colspan="2"><span>Reys, I agree with your theory.  Unforunately, there are very very few wizards that have a comparable level bard to you, that study the songlist, read the boards, and make the most out of their bards.  If they do have a bard, it is likely they got to level 27 at the most and got bored meleeing and playing their song(s) for a group, and never learned to get beyond that.  
<br />

<br />
I have never found a toon x class that played a bard as well as 90% of us here (10% fudge factor).  Actually, once I ran into a cleric that told me that they had a 45ish level bard.  They just wondered what I was twisting and how I liked playing my bard all the time.  He didn't complain once, other than at the end to send me a tell saying he was impressed that my twist never dropped.
<br />

<br />
