				<td colspan="2"><span>My group line-up is simple:
<br />

<br />
Haste (max % if no spell haste, rousing rondo if there is)
<br />
Vah Shir
<br />
Cantana
<br />
Other buff (Katta/Resist/Snare/Lull/OOS/etc)
<br />
OOS/Lull This and above slot reserved for pulling songs when lull is used.
<br />
Mez
<br />
Mem-blur (for when I pull a bit too much aggro)
<br />
Other (Selos, AoE fear, Highsun, etc....usually a 'save-us' song)
<br />

<br />
Thats it...I never change it, and if its an EXP group, and that isn't the most benificial songs, I usually wont stay cause that would mean i have a bad group.
<br />

<br />
On raids I sing:
<br />

<br />
Buff Haste
<br />
Vah Shir
<br />
Cantana/Chorus
<br />
Resist Chorus
<br />
OOS
<br />
Resist Chorus
<br />
Mem-Blur
<br />
Mez
<br />

<br />
Again, always the same.  After playing a long time, I have narrowed it down to the few songs that provide the maximum benifit in group/multigroup situations, and keep it the same.  When I switch things up, I tend to hit the wrong key, and mez something that I didnt mean, do AoE buffs that hit the FD puller and train the raid when he gets smacked with a train and FD's....etc.  Keeping it the same makes me a better bard, and doesnt make any room for requests.
<br />

<br />
